question: What is killing eve about?
answer:
oh god how do i even summarize it… it’s an lgbt thriller about an MI5 officer (eve) who is basically hating her job/life and she notices a pattern of murders and begins to track down this assassin nicknamed villanelle with the help of a secret MI6 team. then they both become kind of obsessed with each other? it’s really hard to summarize but it’s SO good and does an excellent job balancing suspense/tension, comedy, and romance.

plus it’s gay as hell lmao.

She’s totally focused, yet almost entirely inaccessible.”

summary: soft!villanelle season 2 headcanon: eve is going to lose all of her hair.  the one part of herself she actually likes. she gets...
body:
soft!villanelle season 2 headcanon:

eve is going to lose all of her hair. 

the one part of herself she actually likes. she gets compliments on it all the time. it’s going to fall out by the end of the year, and she will be bald. maybe that would teach villanelle a lesson. 

of course, it was partly her idea to recruit villanelle because she is the only person that can help them, but holy SHIT is she a little ASSHOLE.

take yesterday, eve is just minding her own business, working at her desk, learning about assassins, and villanelle is spinning in a rolling chair all around the room. like a fucking 4 year old. and then see, she gets a hold of a pen, and she keeps. clicking. it. for an hour, no matter how many times eve tells her to stop she’s just clicking. the. pen.

villanelle knows what she’s doing. eve knows she knows. she fucking winks and does that stupid smile thing with the dimple and god–

eve is going to murder her. she already tried, but she’s really going to do it this time, okay?

and so, eve relishes in her mornings, the time before she has to go deal with an assassin that has the attention span of a kindergartner. she goes to her coffee shop, gets a latte and a croissant, and takes the long way to work. it’s pleasant.

she pushes open the door, and the bell rings. “hi eve,” jack, the barista, calls from the back.

“hey, jack. how are you?” she responds lopping her bag onto the counter.

“the usual?”

eve nods.

jack starts preparing her order. “im doin’ well. how about yourself?”

eve turns and leans against the counter. “oh well im-“

no.

NO.

FUCK NO.

villanelle is sitting on a chair by the window, drinking a beautifully designed cappuccino. she gives eve a small wave and a devilish grin.

“terrible. im terrible.”

jack returns to the counter. “that’s a shame. five pounds, please.” eve takes her drink and gives jack the money and then some. he thanks her, but she’s not paying attention, her eyes trained on villanelle. she marches over.

“you.”

villanelle takes another sip of her drink, gazing innocently at eve with her wide, doe eyes. “me.”

“what are you doing here?” she sneers. 

“enjoying a coffee before i head to the office.”

“why.”

“because i like coffee and this place makes it,” she replies, lazily leaning back.

“this place.”

“yes.”

“this is my place.”

“i don’t think you own it, eve.” she points at jack. “he does.”

eve is two seconds away from punching her in the face.

“i know what you’re doing,” eve growls.

“and what would that be?” she blinks.

“stalking me. annoying me. bothering me.”

villanelle laughs. it’s obnoxious. “don’t flatter yourself, eve.”

she looks at eve’s croissant and latte. “you should drink that before it gets cold. cold lattes are bleh.” eve hates how fucking adorable she looks when she sticks her tongue out. it’s not fair. 

eve throws her a tight smile and obliges. she was going to drink it anyway. 

villanelle stands up, and eve has to step to the side because their chests nearly touch, and villanelle has no concept of personal space. she begins packing up her things and throws on her cost. “would you like to walk to work, eve? since we’re here together and all.”

“no.”

villanelle pouts. “come on, eve. it’s the same way! you know…” she proceeds to list out the exact route eve takes every day. eve nearly chokes on her croissant.

aha! “so you HAVE been stalking me,” eve says like she caught villanelle for something she wouldn’t typically do. she should have known better. that this absolute dick would invade every facet of her life. it’s really her own fault for thinking she could enjoy something. 

“i prefer the term ‘admiring from afar.’ you do have a great arse.” villanelle shamelessly drags her eyes up and down eve’s body.

eve wasn’t expecting that. “i-um…. oh.”

villanelle snickers. “so you’ll walk with me?” eve is silent. “pleeeeaaaaaaase,” villanelle pouts.

eve can’t believe she’s doing this. she really can’t.

“… fine.”

“YES!” villanelle claps her hands together. “we can do this every morning!”

“no, no. not every morning just this morning.”

she just laughs. “whatever you say, eve.”

villanelle slips past her and heads for the door. eve follows closely behind.

they’re about to leave when —

“eve!”

eve whips around. it’s jack. he’s holding another coffee. “for your bad day. on the house.”

“oh my god. thank you. you’re a lifesaver. you don’t know how much i needed this.” eve snatches it from him. she could kiss this man. her gratitude could never be expressed in words, but she hopes the desperation etched on her face does it for her. 

jack smiles. “you and your girlfriend are cute. the little bickering. i remember when my husband and i used to fight like that.”

eve’s eyes go wide. “she’s not-“

eve looks back to villanelle who is tapping her foot impatiently outside. she makes a let’s go gesture.

eve sighs. “i’ll see you tomorrow.”

“bye, eve!”

the bell rings as she walks out.

take yesterday, eve is just minding her own business, working at her desk, learning about assassins, and villanelle is spinning in a rolling chair all around the room. like a fucking 4 year old. and then see, she gets a hold of a pen, and she keeps. clicking. it. for an hour, no matter how many times eve tells her to stop she’s just clicking. the. pen.

villanelle knows what she’s doing. eve knows she knows. she fucking winks and does that stupid smile thing with the dimple and god–

eve is going to murder her. she already tried, but she’s really going to do it this time, okay?

and so, eve relishes in her mornings, the time before she has to go deal with an assassin that has the attention span of a kindergartner. she goes to her coffee shop, gets a latte and a croissant, and takes the long way to work. it’s pleasant.

she pushes open the door, and the bell rings. “hi eve,” jack, the barista, calls from the back.

“hey, jack. how are you?” she responds lopping her bag onto the counter.

“the usual?”

eve nods.

jack starts preparing her order. “im doin’ well. how about yourself?”

eve turns and leans against the counter. “oh well im-“

no.

NO.

FUCK NO.

villanelle is sitting on a chair by the window, drinking a beautifully designed cappuccino. she gives eve a small wave and a devilish grin.

“terrible. im terrible.”

jack returns to the counter. “that’s a shame. five pounds, please.” eve takes her drink and gives jack the money and then some. he thanks her, but she’s not paying attention, her eyes trained on villanelle. she marches over.

“you.”

villanelle takes another sip of her drink, gazing innocently at eve with her wide, doe eyes. “me.”

“what are you doing here?” she sneers. 

“enjoying a coffee before i head to the office.”

“why.”

“because i like coffee and this place makes it,” she replies, lazily leaning back.

“this place.”

“yes.”

“this is my place.”

“i don’t think you own it, eve.” she points at jack. “he does.”

eve is two seconds away from punching her in the face.

“i know what you’re doing,” eve growls.

“and what would that be?” she blinks.

“stalking me. annoying me. bothering me.”

villanelle laughs. it’s obnoxious. “don’t flatter yourself, eve.”

she looks at eve’s croissant and latte. “you should drink that before it gets cold. cold lattes are bleh.” eve hates how fucking adorable she looks when she sticks her tongue out. it’s not fair. 

eve throws her a tight smile and obliges. she was going to drink it anyway. 

villanelle stands up, and eve has to step to the side because their chests nearly touch, and villanelle has no concept of personal space. she begins packing up her things and throws on her cost. “would you like to walk to work, eve? since we’re here together and all.”

“no.”

villanelle pouts. “come on, eve. it’s the same way! you know…” she proceeds to list out the exact route eve takes every day. eve nearly chokes on her croissant.

aha! “so you HAVE been stalking me,” eve says like she caught villanelle for something she wouldn’t typically do. she should have known better. that this absolute dick would invade every facet of her life. it’s really her own fault for thinking she could enjoy something. 

“i prefer the term ‘admiring from afar.’ you do have a great arse.” villanelle shamelessly drags her eyes up and down eve’s body.

eve wasn’t expecting that. “i-um…. oh.”

villanelle snickers. “so you’ll walk with me?” eve is silent. “pleeeeaaaaaaase,” villanelle pouts.

eve can’t believe she’s doing this. she really can’t.

“… fine.”

“YES!” villanelle claps her hands together. “we can do this every morning!”

“no, no. not every morning just this morning.”

she just laughs. “whatever you say, eve.”

villanelle slips past her and heads for the door. eve follows closely behind.

they’re about to leave when —

“eve!”

eve whips around. it’s jack. he’s holding another coffee. “for your bad day. on the house.”

“oh my god. thank you. you’re a lifesaver. you don’t know how much i needed this.” eve snatches it from him. she could kiss this man. her gratitude could never be expressed in words, but she hopes the desperation etched on her face does it for her. 

jack smiles. “you and your girlfriend are cute. the little bickering. i remember when my husband and i used to fight like that.”

eve’s eyes go wide. “she’s not-“

eve looks back to villanelle who is tapping her foot impatiently outside. she makes a let’s go gesture.

eve sighs. “i’ll see you tomorrow.”

“bye, eve!”

the bell rings as she walks out.
